-- Peru Stocks: Alturas, Buenaventura, Maple and Panoro Decline
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-03-12T21:39:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-12/peru-stocks-alturas-buenaventura-grana-maple-and-panoro.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for the first time in four
days, losing 1 percent to 22,997.66. The  MSCI All Peru Capped
Index (MXPECAPD)  slid 0.5 percent to 2,895.70.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, dropped 7.7 percent to 12 cents after
copper fell in  New York , said Eduardo Fernandini, a trader at
Lima-based Kallpa Securities SAB.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, slumped 4.8 percent to 80 cents.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the countryâ€™s
biggest precious metals miner, slid 2.5 percent to $39.14 after
gold fell below $1,700 an ounce in New York.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, fell 2.3 percent to $1.27
after crude futures declined in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
